info.name: Restful Booker API Testing
info.description:
This project demonstrates end-to-end API testing of the [Restful Booker API](https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/), a RESTful web service for hotel booking. The testing approach is based on real-world user stories and includes both positive and negative test cases. All tests were executed using **Postman**, covering functionalities such as authentication, booking creation, data retrieval, updates, and deletion.  

#### **Scope & Tools:**

- **Tools Used**: Postman, JSON, REST API, cURL (reference)
    
- **Test Categories**:
    
    - Authentication via Token
        
    - Create, Retrieve, Update & Delete Bookings (CRUD)
        
    - Query Filtering
        
    - Token-based Access Control
        
    - Negative Testing (empty, invalid, malformed inputs)

item.name: Authentication via Token
item.description: As a user, I want to authenticate with valid credentials and receive a token, so that I can perform protected API operations like creating, updating, and deleting bookings.

item.name: Update a Booking

request.description:
Generated from cURL: curl -X PUT \
  https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking/1 \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Cookie: token=abc123' \
  -d '{
    "firstname" : "James",
    "lastname" : "Brown",
    "totalprice" : 111,
    "depositpaid" : true,
    "bookingdates" : {
        "checkin" : "2018-01-01",
        "checkout" : "2019-01-01"
    },
    "additionalneeds" : "Breakfast"
}'

item.description: As a user, I want to update the information of an existing booking using its ID and a valid token, so that I can make changes when needed.
